{"questionId":"9076839","questionHtml":"<p>A compressed spring is used to launch an object along a horizontal frictionless surface. When the&nbsp;spring is compressed through a distance <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and released, the object leaves the spring at speed <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n</math></span>.&nbsp;What is the distance through which the spring must be compressed for the object to leave the&nbsp;spring at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{v}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>v</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0cb5dce4dcdf5af4dd6d5b570a26bd1203de9184.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">A.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{x}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">B.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{x}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">C.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{x}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">D.&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\\sqrt 2 \">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>B</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076839","referenceCode":"18N.1.SL.TZ0.8","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A compressed spring is used to launch an object along a horizontal frictionless surface. When the spring is compressed through a distance x and released, the object leaves the spri","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"8","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics","2.3 – Work, energy, and power","Core","Topic 2: Mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}